This year's exhibition with 4500m2 floor area has an estimated scale of 150+ exhibition booths and 7000+ visitors, along with numerous quality specialized workshops, featuring a specialized product display zones in HVACR field: Commercial & civil air conditioners Industrial air conditioner Humidity treatment Ventilation & air filter Cold chain HVACR control & automation HVAC supplies Components for air conditioner assembling Consulting, design and contractor Specialized organizations Within the framework of the CLEANFACT & RHVAC 2024 event series, there will be a series of specialized seminars on HVACR with the participation of many leading experts and large businesses around the world. This is an opportunity not to be missed because of the diversity of topics and useful solutions coming from leading industry experts at the seminars. Register to attend the below seminars now with different roles such as attendees, speakers, sponsors or organizing exclusive seminars for your business: Eurovent Certita Certification Seminar Cold Supply Chain Seminar In addition, the exhibition also has other accompanying series of events: HVAC Techshow, a contest for HVAC students, Industrial Investment Seminar and Plant maintenance and operation Seminar. Our organizers hope that CLEANFACT & RHVAC Vietnam 2024 will accompany your business in the promotion and business journey of 2024, contributing to trade promotion and industry community development. Register your exhibition booth today to secure a convenient booth location, attract more industry visitors, and enhance your business brand!

20 conferences in one: That's the IT Days! This year, the IT Days are taking place for the tenth time. Around 1200 participants are taking part. More than 220 speakers offer concentrated know-how in 10 parallel tracks over four days. So much for the numbers. But is that really important? Or isn't it actually much more about the content? The annual conference of the specialist magazine Informatik Aktuell aims to provide you with comprehensive training: Not only on your main focus, but also on all the topics surrounding it. Software architecture, development, DevOps, cloud, IT operations, IT security and agile are just some of the topics covered in our sub-conferences. In 10 parallel tracks, you can take part in all workshops, talks and sessions, keynotes and training sessions from morning to evening on the days you have booked - on all topics that you find exciting. We offer deep dives: we go into depth, practical and well-founded. So if you're looking for intensive training, you've come to the right place! In addition to the technical topics, we also focus on other areas: IT and society, New Work, but also ethical aspects and the question "How do we all shape our future?" are areas in which we want to develop visions and encourage reflection. In addition to your intellectual well-being, we also care about your mental and physical well-being. We serve all coffee specialties, from espresso and cappuccino to latte macchiato. We also offer a comprehensive and delicious catering service. If you have any intolerances or would like vegan or vegetarian food, we will provide everything you need. Our supporting program is special. Last year there was a retro computer exhibition, table football against the world champion, interactive discussion rounds, a science slam, business yoga or simply a nice after-work beer. Just as you like it. We are currently working on the new supporting program and will surprise you. It will be worth it! Curious? Then register and join us!

Implementing the Common Information Model to Support the Seamless Integration of Multiple Operational Systems and Flexibility Market Players 5-Day In-Person Conference, Exhibition & Networking Forum21-25 March 2022 | London, UK The 3rd annual IEC CIM Week 2022 conference, exhibition and networking forum draws together CIM implementation leaders from across the power sector to share insights on the optimal application of the standard within the utility environment, between different utilities, and with a broad range of flexibility market players. Through a series of utility case-study presentations and supplier innovation discussions we highlight the aspects of CIM that need further development to make it truly fit for purpose, identify the lessons learnt from CIM implementations across a wide rage of operational systems, discuss the effectiveness of validation tools and processes, and address how CIM can be fully leveraged to support DER integration and data exchange with a range of critical infrastructure players. Finally, we address the security and privacy issues that will strike the balance between data availability and privacy. By the end of this week-long programme participants will have a thorough understanding of the fundamental building blocks of CIM, clarity on the cost-benefit and how to devise a business plan and implementation roadmap to secure long term investment in CIM, and full awareness of how CIM enabled systems must be secured to ensure you achieve regulatory and legal compliance.
